3 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
4 Sec. 1. 29 V.S.A. § 165 is amended to read:
5 § 165. SPACE ALLOCATION, INVENTORY, AND USE; LEASING
6 PROPERTY; COMMISSIONER’S PREAPPROVAL REQUIRED
7 * * *
8 (e) The Commissioner of Buildings and General Services shall maintain an
9 inventory of all State-owned buildings and land and shall biannually compile
10 and update the information received under subsection (g) of this section, which
11 shall be considered once available in making spacing allocations and
12 designating uses under subsection (c) of this section.
13 * * *
14 (g) The head of each agency shall prepare and forward to the
15 Commissioner of Buildings and General Services when requested by the
16 Commissioner annually in a format prescribed by the Commissioner an
17 inventory of: square footage available for use; square footage in actual use;
18 square footage not in use; square footage used for storage; square footage that
19 is unfinished; cost per square foot for rent; cost per square foot for operation
20 and maintenance; and the source of funds for rent, operation, and maintenance,
21 including the act and section numbers of a legislative directive if applicable.
